Hey - I've found 4 issues, and left some high level feedback:

- In `buildPodDisruptionBudget`, consider making the replicas=0 case explicit (e.g. no PDB or a distinct policy) so that the behavior is clearly defined when Keystone is scaled to zero replicas instead of falling through to the single-replica branch.
- In `EnsurePDB`, you always update the existing object’s spec regardless of whether it has actually changed; you could follow the DeepCopy-and-compare pattern used elsewhere in the codebase to avoid unnecessary updates on every reconcile.
- `EnsurePDB` only sets the controller owner reference on create; if the owner ref is removed or changed out-of-band, it will never be restored, so you may want to enforce/refresh the owner reference on the update path as well.

